  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community-based Climate Change Adaptation and Resiliency in Maguindanao (CCCHARM)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Specifically, the proposed project aims to:
1. Increase understanding of the target population on the hazards and vulnerabilities to floods
2. Strengthen capacity of community associations and BLGU to address hazards and vulnerabilities to floods
3. Increase the participation of the communities in the decision making process at the barangay government level
4. Provide selected poor families and community associations with flood-resilient and environmentally-friendly livelihoods</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#xB7; increasing people&#x2019;s awareness on hazards to floods; 
&#xB7; establishing community emergency response team to have a community-based structure that will respond during emergencies; 
&#xB7; installing early warning system to aid people on preparedness measures; and 
&#xB7; developing disaster risk reduction and management plan to guide the barangay government and the community people on specific activities and projects on disaster preparedness, response and management  in the area.</narrative>
  </description>
